values:
So here is the update.I've been down for about two and half months and I'm trying to decide if I like it or not. There are many beautiful men here they are all gay at least the ones I know. But you know what? I miss my straight friends. Is that possible to have more in common with my straight friends than I do my gay friends. Here everyone seems so plastic. I like the faster pace of things a little intimidating in the lifestyle department but it seems that things are going well. I'm in school I start next tuesday. I'm steady looking for work. I've even gone low rent and tried fast food joints. I'm having alot more mood swings here than I ever did in jacksonville. I'm either very happy or very sad there doesn't seem to be a middle ground. I have alot of ideas in the art department and I've done a little sketching here but no finished pieces like at home I liken that to the fact that I don't have any more bristol paper. 

Bill is ok works alot. The only negative thing is that all we do is sit at home. I want to go do stuff at least in jacksonville there was st augie or Orlando wasn't far away but not work is providing so many limits that I think I'm home sick more often than not. Hopefully once school has started and I have something to do that feeling will leave.

Now for the comedy. Funny shit that goes on here. The white guy with a nasty profile explaining he doesn't like black&nbsp;guys&nbsp;goes on a job interview the next guy the guy interviewing him is the one he blocked for saying hello to him. I over heard this next one at a table and I started laughing my ass off. &quot;You know what I hate white guys who come up to you and say &quot;I'm not really into black guys but your really hot&quot; just great your feeling abnormal and I just happen to be black what a&nbsp;perfect introduction&nbsp;line&quot;
